summary: Oo oo!! 📂 for shishida, Juzo, shihai, and kamakiri?
question: Oo oo!! 📂 for shishida, Juzo, shihai, and kamakiri?
answer:
One per boyooo

- Shishida’s grades are surprisingly not very high. He might use fancy words and his handwriting might be very pretty, his grades are sadly not brilliant. But he is very hard-working, good luck Shishida !!

- Honenuki has accidentally activated his quirk before. During an especially complex exam he melted his table, and it took quite a long time to get him to deactivate it and to get the table in its normal form again (he wasn’t even able to do it himself under stress: Monoma had to copy his quirk to undo its effects). He who is always calm and flexible, he does have these small moments of inattention or utter panick…

- Kuroiro loves wearing white clothes because pure white on black can actually be painful for the eye… and edgy boy is a little piece of shit who likes making people suffer

- Kamakiri struggles to put sunglasses on, although he absolutely loves them. His face is not… sunglass-friendly to say the least, and it’s a shame (really is) -mod copycat

summary:
INKTOBER DAY 30: Midoriya Izuku x Bakugou Katsuki, Unity
Alright, so let me explain on this one.
Today is the 100th anniversary...
body:
INKTOBER DAY 30: Midoriya Izuku x Bakugou Katsuki, Unity

Alright, so let me explain on this one.

Today is the 100th anniversary of my nation declaring autonomy and officially connecting with another nation into one country (Czechoslovakia) to be freed from Austria-Hungary.

To achieve this troops had to be sent to 6 countries who fought against Austria-Hungary.

And these are the uniforms some of the soldiers wore while fighting along those countries!

I basically wanted to do something patriotic since on this day 100 years ago my nation got recognised as independent for the first time in history (even though that alliance still didn’t guarantee total freedom for us.)

The nations later separated into two different countries, but this history will always exist and should be remembered.

The reason why I chose these two is that they have their differences and history of not getting along, but in the end they have to unite against bigger enemy and grow stronger together; and that really sounds like the story of these two nations!
